  "type": "mcq",
  "title": "Magnetic field - near a current-carrying wire",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two wires positioned perpendicularly to each other. Wire 1 is vertical and carries current I toward the bottom of the page. Wire 2 is perpendicular to the plane of the page, and current I is indicated.\" src=\"/images/c411b7a926368db868aaaceb7f0f351f.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two current carrying wires are arranged as shown. Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> carries a current <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I\"><math alttext=\"I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>I</mi></math></span></span> directed toward the bottom of the page. Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is positioned to the right of Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and is oriented perpendicular to Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>. Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> carries a current <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I\"><math alttext=\"I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>I</mi></math></span></span> out of the page. Which of the following correctly describes the net force exerted on Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> by Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and provides the correct justification?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i2",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> experiences no net force from Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> because Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is oriented perpendicular to Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and there are no forces exerted on Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> experiences no net force from Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> because the forces exerted on Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> by Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> sum to zero.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The net force on Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> will point toward Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> because the magnetic field produced by Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> in the region containing Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> produces a net force on Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> to the left by the right hand rule.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The net force on Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> will point toward Wire <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> because current carrying wires placed near each other will always attract each other.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
  },
